    "# 01 Data Processing\n",
    "\n",
    "## What this stage does\n",
    "Loads raw Yelp JSON data, filters for the city of Philadelphia, applies a minimum of 50 reviews threshold, and joins the business, user, and review data into a combined view.\n",
    "\n",
    "## Input tables/files required\n",
    "- `yelp_academic_dataset_business.json`\n",
    "- `yelp_academic_dataset_review.json`\n",
    "- `yelp_academic_dataset_user.json`\n",
    "\n",
    "## Output tables/files produced\n",
    "- `merged_philly` (Temp View)\n",
    "- `businesses_filtered` (Temp View)\n",
    "\n",
    "## Key parameters to configure\n",
    "- `CITY_FILTER`: 'Philadelphia'\n",
    "- `MIN_REVIEWS`: 50\n",
    "\n",
    "## Expected runtime\n",
    "- ~10-15 minutes on Databricks Community Edition."
   ]
